@startuml
!include ../style.puml

title Transaction Lifecycle In distrib-txn-db

' [step1 {"name":"Begin creates a coordinator record"}]
actor "Application" as app
participant "Txn Client" as client
participant "Coordinator\nhash(txnId)" as coord
participant "Participant\nhash(key)" as part

app -> client: begin txn
client -> coord: BeginTransaction(txnId)
activate coord
coord -> coord: create TxnRecord(status=PENDING,\nreadTimestamp, participants=[])
coord --> client: BeginTransactionResponse
deactivate coord
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Writes create intents"}]
app -> client: write key=account-101
client -> part: TxnWrite(txnId, key, value, readTs)
activate part
part -> part: store IntentRecord in intentStore
part --> client: TxnWriteResponse(success)
deactivate part
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Reads use snapshot plus own intents"}]
app -> client: read account-101
client -> part: TxnRead(txnId, key, readTs)
activate part
part -> part: if own intent exists,\nreturn own provisional value
part -> part: else read committedStore\nas of readTimestamp
part --> client: TxnReadResponse
deactivate part
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Commit marks record committed"}]
app -> client: commit txn
client -> coord: Commit(txnId, participantWrites)
activate coord
coord -> coord: mark TxnRecord COMMITTED\nchoose commitTimestamp
coord -> part: ResolveTransaction(txnId,\ncommitTimestamp, keys)
activate part
part -> part: move intents to committedStore
part -> part: delete provisional records
part --> coord: ResolveTransactionResponse
deactivate part
coord --> client: CommitResponse(commitTimestamp)
deactivate coord
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Later readers lazily resolve old intents"}]
note over coord, part
If a read/write later finds another transaction's intent,
it asks the coordinator for status and resolves the intent lazily.
That keeps the workshop flow realistic without adding background cleanup daemons.
end note
' [/step5]

@enduml
